    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Quantum entanglement doesn't involve sending a signal through space faster than light; rather, it involves a mysterious connection between particles that transcends our classical understanding of space and time. When two particles become entangled, their properties become linked in such a way that the state of one particle instantly determines the state of the other, regardless of the distance between them. This doesn't mean that information is being transmitted faster than light; instead, the entangled particles share a joint state that is defined by their combined properties.\n\nThe exact mechanism behind this phenomenon is still a subject of research and debate in physics, but it doesn't rely on any known physical process that would violate the speed of light limitation. It's more about the nature of reality at the quantum level, where particles can be deeply interconnected in ways that don't have direct analogs in our everyday experiences. The \"spooky\" part comes from the fact that this connection seems to defy our classical understanding of causality and locality, and we're still working to fully understand the underlying principles at play.",
